7|Warranties & Disclaimers — New Clause §7 with four-layer architecture (express limited warranty → AI-specific disclaimers → broad implied warranty disclaimer → FTC substantiation compliance). Added MN case law (Fahrendorff v. North Homes, Campion). Added FTC AI-washing enforcement analysis with substantiation risk table. Added "as-is" clause analysis for services. Added disclaimer conspicuity guidance. Added SOW drafting guidelines ("say what you can prove" principle). Cross-referenced to MSA §5 and Clause Genome §4, §15, §23. Updated version 1.7.0→1.8.0.